data.comment: Today's referee, Serdar Gozubuyuk, has blown to start the match.
Goal! Queensy Menig gives Enschede a 1-0 lead.
In the minute 29, Danilo puts the ball in the net and the home team extend their lead. The score-line now reads 2-0.
Goal! Enschede extend their lead to 3-0 through Wout Brama.
Vaclav Cerny instrumental with a fine assist.
In the minute 36, The away team replace Thomas Lam with Marc Olivier Doue.
The first-half has come to a close in Enschede.
The whistle has gone to start the second-half.
In the minute 46, John Stegeman (Zwolle) is making a second substitution, with Mike Van Duinen replacing Reza Ghoochannejhad.
Kik Pierie is booked for the home team.
Goal! Vaclav Cerny extends Enschede's lead to 4-0.
In the minute 51, That's a fine assist from Danilo.
Jesper Drost is replacing Clint Leemans for the away team.
The away team have replaced Rico Strieder with Thomas Van Den Belt. This is the fourth substitution made today by John Stegeman.
In the minute 69, Gijs Smal is on a sub for Jayden Oosterwolde for Enschede.
Enschede make their second substitution with Casper Staring replacing Kik Pierie.
Goal! Eliano Reijnders pulls one back to make it 4-1.
In the minute 74, Jesper Drost with an assist there.
Samir Lagsir is replacing Dean Huiberts for Zwolle at Grolsch Veste Stadium.
Ron Jans is making the team's third substitution at Grolsch Veste Stadium with Luka Ilic replacing Jesse Bosch.
In the minute 83, Enschede make their fourth substitution with Halil Dervisoglu replacing Vaclav Cerny.
Enschede take a comfortable 5-1 lead thanks to Luka Ilic.
Great play from Tyronne Ebuehi to set up the goal.
In the minute 88, Ramiz Zerrouki is replacing Godfried Roemeratoe for the home team.
The second-half is over. The match ends 5-1.
